Metropolitan Avenue, at the N.E. corner of Sixty-ninth Avenue, showing in three views the home of Col. Hunt. Owners of this property and house were Thomas Hunt, 1860-73; J. Hunt, 1891; Hunt Estate, 1896; Thomas Hunt, 1909; and the Pennsylvania Railroad in 1923. One Wolfert was the occupant in 1922. The house was demolished in February 1925. View No. 3 is a side view of the house.

October 1923
Views 2&3: April 1923.
